# OpenPort 🔍

A lightweight, multi-threaded Python port scanner with banner grabbing and file export.

> *"No bullshit. Just open ports."*

---

## 🚀 Features

- Multi-threaded scanning (fast)
- Supports domain and IP input
- Banner grabbing from open ports (HTTP, SSH, etc.)
- User-friendly defaults (just press Enter)
- Saves results to timestamped `.txt` files
- No external dependencies — just Python 3

---

## 📦 Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/OpenPort.git
cd OpenPort

    No additional packages required — uses only Python's standard library.

🧑‍💻 Usage
bash

python3 openport.py

You'll be prompted to enter:
text

Enter IP or domain: scanme.nmap.org
Start port (default 1):
End port (default 1024):
Number of threads (default 100):

Press Enter to accept defaults, or type your own values.
